<h2>FAQ ‚Äî quick answers</h2>
<details><summary>Does server country affect privacy?</summary><div>Partly. No-logs policy and provider jurisdiction matter most. Country mainly impacts content access and speed.</div></details>
<details><summary>Nearest server is slow ‚Äî what now?</summary><div>Try another node in the same country or switch protocol (WireGuard ‚Üî OpenVPN). At peak hours, test 2‚Äì3 nearby regions.</div></details>
<details><summary>Best server for Netflix?</summary><div>A <em>Streaming</em> node in the USA or UK. If blocked, change city or server.</div></details>
<details><summary>Best server for torrents?</summary><div><em>P2P</em> servers with proper routing and no port blocks. Enable Kill Switch; avoid Double VPN if you need speed.</div></details>
<details><summary>Use Double VPN daily?</summary><div>You can, but it‚Äôs slower. Save it for anonymity-first tasks, not streaming/gaming.</div></details>
<details><summary>Does VPN change ping in games?</summary><div>Yes ‚Äî sometimes better, sometimes worse, depending on routes. Experiment with regions.</div></details>

<h2>Summary</h2>
<p><strong>There‚Äôs no single ‚Äúbest‚Äù server.</strong> Choose based on your goal and line quality. Gaming/banking ‚Äî local low-ping node. VOD ‚Äî the library‚Äôs country. P2P ‚Äî P2P servers. Maximum privacy ‚Äî obfuscated or Double VPN. Test, compare, save favourites.</p>

